School
district solicitor John Freund said the district had the backing of the
National School Boards Association and the Pennsylvania School Board 
Association. He said they and other organisations are 'concerned about 
the implications of a hyper-sexualised environment,' The Express-Times 
reported.

The lone board member to vote against the appeal said the district should just drop the matter.

'I think we should be done with it. Let it go. We lost 20, 30 times, I don't even know anymore,' Frank Pintabone said.

Easton
is one of several school districts around the country to ban the 
